results.name: Least m such that phi(x)=2m has exactly n solutions.
comment: Sequence refers to the rank of the first occurrence of n in A032446.
formula: a(n) = A007374(n)/2 for n > 2. - _David Wasserman_, Feb 09 2005
example: a(0) = 7. Carmichael conjectured that a(1) doesn't exist.
